I don't get all the hate for Byleth joining smash. When Three houses was released, i immediately wondered wether the protagonist would ever be in Smash. Now that they did i was ecstatic and giddy and played Smash for the first time in a while, enjoying trying out the new character. If you don't like it, don't play it, doesn't mean nobody else can enjoy the game at their own pace, with their own preference. There's plenty of people who hate other characters for an equally, if not more justifiable reason. That doesn't mean nobody else can enjoy playing them...
Isn't that what it is all about in the end? Playing a game for enjoyment? Nobody is forcing you to play the new characters lol They could just as easily not make new characters at all and pull a fifa with 5 new characters in next year's release of the same game xd

Hey, wait a minute: the Final Smash is called "Progenitor God Ruptured Heaven". It sounds like it is based on the "Ruptured Heaven" skill from Three Houses.

Here is what I dont get, though: during the Final Smash, Byleth's hair becomes green. In Three Houses, Byleth's hair turns green once he/she and Sothis fuse together. During that time, "Ruptured Heaven" is replaced by the upgraded skill "Sublime Heaven".

So by that logic, shouldn't the Final Smash be called "Progenitor God Sublime Heaven?"

snippet.textDisplay:
Byleth is mainly disappointing for the following reasons

- feels like an ad/ marketing shoved down your throat...its the last pick for the fighters pass so they knew everyone would be waiting with extreme anticipation for something crazy. If byleth had been announced early or during the games release it wouldn't have Been as bad

-its another sword/ranged character...BUT MORE SO it's another swordie from Fire emblem ... which already has 7 reps WHICH (for the most part) all play similarly.

- to any one who says " Mario and pokemon have more reps so what?"

Mario and pokemon are STAPLES to Nintendo...all of their characters look AND play differently. Almost all cultures around the world can easily recognize these 2 series immediately. I love anime but biased aside all of the fire emblem characters look similar and play similarly.

Mario, peach, bowser jr, piranha plant, wario, and bowser are all familiar to anyone who has every played a video game and none of them play alike.

Pikachu, jigglypuff, lucario, incineroar, and mewtwo all look different, while still being recognizable and play completely different from each other

Lucina looks like girl version of marth and has the same exact move set. Roy looks similar with just red hair....not to mention he was built as a echo for marth so his move set is super similar....chrome is an echo of roy. Ike is just heavy version of marth. Corrin is actually pretty different but really they just space with sword in neutral soooo still pretty similar.....

Robin is the only one who is actually different.....byleth looks just like marth and lucina. They will probably play somewhat like cross between link and marth....there's just no need for this character I feel

- its taking up a spot for someone else

- its not a 3rd party guest which, based on reggie's words from the game awards last year, was expected for the whole pass

At this point I'm more disappointed that this came after 4 out of nowhere choices that people would have thought improbable in other smash titles....with a pick everyone knew was coming anyway. Like I knew Byleth would happen at some point because "New FE game, gotta shove the newest protagonist in smash for advertisement" but this was a really poor placement. I legitimately think something else was planned and something had to be changed. Because ending the first fighter pass with four unexpected third parties and one...very expected first party doesn't make a whole ton of sense.


The fact FE is already a bit of an over represented franchise in smash with half of the roster or so playing next to identical with each other doesn't really help that. Byleth honestly shoulda just been Fighter 1 in Pass 2.

snippet.textDisplay: I loved this, Sakurai! I've never played any of the fire emblem games, but Byleth's style of combat is very satisfying and his weaponry make him a formidable looking opponent! Although it was another Fire Emblem character, people have to realize it was a character we've never heard of. And I sure haven't. Also, the Cuphead Mii costume was very surprising. I did not expect him now having the game on the switch. I feel like this new character will be a welcome edition and will be a great completion to Challenger pack 1. If I were to rate this character on a scale on 1-10, it would be almost a 9.
